1
00:00:00,880 --> 00:00:03,240
I want to do it.

2
00:00:04,040 --> 00:00:05,670
I want to have s...

3
00:00:08,910 --> 00:00:10,540
"S"?

4
00:00:15,130 --> 00:00:20,600
Soap. I'll go wash my hands with soap.

5
00:00:26,850 --> 00:00:30,320
I can't ask about sex the moment he wakes up.

6
00:00:30,320 --> 00:00:32,630
Nope. Definitely not.

7
00:00:32,630 --> 00:00:34,270
But...

8
00:00:36,280 --> 00:00:40,360
Maybe if I pop the question
at the right timing?

9
00:00:44,690 --> 00:00:46,240
Ouji.

10
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:52,700
Do you... want to drink some wine?

11
00:00:53,660 --> 00:00:55,980
Sure, let's crack open a bottle.

12
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:58,780
Alright.

13
00:00:58,780 --> 00:01:01,020
<i>I was super nervous.</i>

14
00:01:01,020 --> 00:01:04,300
<i>I was just saying whatever at some point.</i>

15
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:07,200
<i>Thankfully, Saiki helped fill in the gaps.</i>

16
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:09,170
I'm being hired as this girl's producer.

17
00:01:09,170 --> 00:01:13,750
Really? I see her in a ton of magazines.

18
00:01:15,210 --> 00:01:18,880
Do you think she's cute?

19
00:01:20,190 --> 00:01:23,250
Not really.

20
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:27,610
<i>"Then who do you think is cute?"</i>

21
00:01:27,610 --> 00:01:29,160
<i>"Me?"</i>

22
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:31,180
<i>Perfect. The natural follow-up question.</i>

23
00:01:31,880 --> 00:01:34,180
<i>Or is it?</i>

24
00:01:34,180 --> 00:01:36,480
No, you're deluding yourself.

25
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:38,300
Huh?

26
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:40,960
Nothing.

27
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:42,860
Weirdo.

28
00:01:47,060 --> 00:01:49,520
<i>If anything...</i>

29
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:53,410
Do you even have a sex drive now?

30
00:02:52,230 --> 00:02:56,920
[Episode 3]

31
00:02:56,920 --> 00:03:00,640
Do you even have a sex drive now?

32
00:03:01,820 --> 00:03:03,410
Huh?

33
00:03:03,410 --> 00:03:05,360
A sex drive?

34
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:06,940
Me?

35
00:03:07,880 --> 00:03:12,170
- I misspoke.
- Really? I'm not entirely convinced.

36
00:03:12,170 --> 00:03:15,910
Sorry, my brain's a mess right now, and...

37
00:03:15,910 --> 00:03:20,040
Honestly, not for these last few years, no.

38
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:22,850
- What?
- Maybe it's my age.

39
00:03:22,850 --> 00:03:25,150
I was a little too active in my youth.

40
00:03:25,150 --> 00:03:28,600
You... You think?

41
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:31,210
Well, that's not the only reason.

42
00:03:31,870 --> 00:03:35,300
It's just easy being with you, Haru.

43
00:03:41,950 --> 00:03:43,670
I'm going to bed.

44
00:03:44,710 --> 00:03:46,380
Night.

45
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:05,960
<i>Being with you is so easy.</i>

46
00:04:10,050 --> 00:04:12,440
That doesn't make me happy at all.

47
00:04:37,330 --> 00:04:40,470
I'll go fill the bath for us.

48
00:04:41,970 --> 00:04:43,740
Okay.

49
00:04:52,830 --> 00:04:54,400
[6 Months Earlier]

50
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:56,980
I'll be applying your toner.

51
00:04:58,760 --> 00:05:01,850
Yamaguchi, we can't style 20 actors
in an hour!

52
00:05:01,850 --> 00:05:03,330
I promise it's possible.

53
00:05:03,330 --> 00:05:05,980
Some kids do their own finishing touches.

54
00:05:05,980 --> 00:05:09,500
Fuyumi, how's my eyeliner? Looking good?

55
00:05:11,030 --> 00:05:13,810
They're not even in the slightest.

56
00:05:15,220 --> 00:05:17,470
Show me how I can improve.

57
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:33,950
<i>I won't expect results,
or anything in return.</i>

58
00:05:33,950 --> 00:05:38,670
<i>I'm simply letting my heart and body
savor this moment.</i>

59
00:05:38,670 --> 00:05:44,400
<i>Affirming myself in this manner,
is so alleviating.</i>

60
00:05:46,650 --> 00:05:48,680
What a poet.

61
00:05:52,430 --> 00:05:55,350
[Haru: I failed...]

62
00:06:03,660 --> 00:06:08,360
Was that notification from your husband?

63
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:11,450
Nope. A friend.

64
00:06:12,830 --> 00:06:17,440
She had this long,
one-sided crush on a musician,

65
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:19,840
only for him to suddenly propose to her.

66
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:22,150
They got married the other day.

67
00:06:22,150 --> 00:06:25,190
Sounds like a story out of a fairy tale.

68
00:06:27,060 --> 00:06:30,080
But it might not be going well for them.

69
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:32,940
Why not?
Isn't this their "happily ever after"?

70
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:41,540
Life doesn't "end" so simply like in stories.

71
00:06:42,740 --> 00:06:45,320
Romance, marriage,

72
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:50,460
both can become shackles
if you're fixated on them.

73
00:06:58,340 --> 00:07:00,390
What the...

74
00:07:00,390 --> 00:07:05,000
You were thinking of your husband.

75
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,790
That makes me jealous.

76
00:07:08,180 --> 00:07:12,450
Will you stay the night today?

77
00:07:14,530 --> 00:07:16,480
I can't.

78
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:18,590
I'll go home.

79
00:07:19,430 --> 00:07:22,790
You have a photoshoot tomorrow.

80
00:07:22,790 --> 00:07:26,370
You need to sleep early, and prep.

81
00:07:26,370 --> 00:07:29,620
You're not my stylist tomorrow though.

82
00:07:29,620 --> 00:07:32,000
I have other jobs to do.

83
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:35,320
I'm not your exclusive makeup artist, Shota.

84
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:38,720
I'll become famous enough to request for you.

85
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:40,460
Don't mix business
with personal matters, okay?

86
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:43,140
I wasn't trying to mix them together.

87
00:07:43,140 --> 00:07:45,980
Sure, I may have a slightly ulterior motive.

88
00:07:48,150 --> 00:07:51,600
But when you did my makeup for a shoot,

89
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:54,160
it was a smash hit.

90
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:55,640
- Really?
- Yeah.

91
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:58,020
People said I looked sexy.

92
00:07:59,170 --> 00:08:00,790
That's good to hear.

93
00:08:00,790 --> 00:08:02,710
I owe it to your magic touch.

94
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:09,820
You don't need to stay the night.

95
00:08:11,070 --> 00:08:14,650
But can you stay a bit longer?

96
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:20,880
Nope.

97
00:08:44,410 --> 00:08:48,530
[Keiko Kotani]
[Having fun "playing marriage"?]

98
00:08:54,140 --> 00:08:55,530
I'm home.

99
00:08:55,530 --> 00:08:57,230
Welcome back!

100
00:08:57,230 --> 00:09:00,040
- Huh?
- Home already?

101
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:03,120
Yeah. I wrapped up earlier today.

102
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:05,140
Chizuka, what happened to your sleepover?

103
00:09:05,140 --> 00:09:09,290
The Sato's called to cancel.
Apparently, Yui caught a fever.

104
00:09:09,290 --> 00:09:11,520
I see.

105
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:13,130
Did you two eat already?

106
00:09:13,130 --> 00:09:16,980
Yeah. We had dinner at a diner.

107
00:09:16,980 --> 00:09:18,820
I see.

108
00:09:28,110 --> 00:09:29,960
Something the matter?

109
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:32,810
Nothing.

110
00:09:33,980 --> 00:09:37,850
Just pondering the big job I finished.

111
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:45,700
Here's to hoping your next job
is catered more to your skills.

112
00:09:45,700 --> 00:09:53,530
You used to style for big advertisements
and major magazines, right?

113
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:58,650
Right.

114
00:09:58,650 --> 00:10:01,240
Maybe I'll lobby for a better opportunity.

115
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:10,370
[New message from Haru]

116
00:10:22,730 --> 00:10:25,660
<i>Do you even have a sex drive now?</i>

117
00:10:25,660 --> 00:10:29,820
<i>Not for these last few years, no.</i>

118
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:31,840
<i>What?</i>

119
00:10:37,740 --> 00:10:39,360
For you.

120
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:41,050
Thanks.

121
00:10:41,050 --> 00:10:42,670
Sleep-deprived?

122
00:10:42,670 --> 00:10:44,860
Maybe I should've bought coffee.

123
00:10:44,860 --> 00:10:46,870
No, you wouldn't drink that.

124
00:10:46,870 --> 00:10:48,270
Yeah.

125
00:10:48,270 --> 00:10:50,400
I don't do well with bitter things.

126
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:52,290
I'm surprised you knew.

127
00:10:52,290 --> 00:10:54,740
We've worked together for a while now.

128
00:10:54,740 --> 00:10:57,070
That, we have.

129
00:10:58,280 --> 00:11:01,370
Something on your mind?

130
00:11:01,370 --> 00:11:03,730
I'm here to listen.

131
00:11:03,730 --> 00:11:09,010
<i>"My newlywed husband has no sex drive."
Like I could just blurt that out.</i>

132
00:11:10,270 --> 00:11:12,830
It's nothing. Thanks though.

133
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:21,200
<i>I can meet for lunch, if you want.</i>
[Fuyumi]

134
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:29,840
You asked him if he had a sex drive?

135
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:36,770
If he's got none, then what do I even do?

136
00:11:36,770 --> 00:11:40,480
Gosh... to think your Ouji has no drive...

137
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:42,310
I don't feel any better, by the way.

138
00:11:42,310 --> 00:11:45,680
You said accepting my feelings would help.

139
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:47,860
If anything, I feel more confused.

140
00:11:47,860 --> 00:11:50,990
I guess I should say, "I'm sorry"?

141
00:11:50,990 --> 00:11:54,360
Even if I want to do it, we can't.

142
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:56,030
He has no sex drive! None!

143
00:11:56,030 --> 00:11:57,920
Inside voices, Haru!

144
00:11:57,920 --> 00:11:59,890
It's still the middle of the day!

145
00:11:59,890 --> 00:12:03,980
I even bought a king-sized bed for my room...

146
00:12:03,980 --> 00:12:09,500
B-But... I think you've actually
made some progress.

147
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:12,860
Until now,
you were thinking about this yourself.

148
00:12:12,860 --> 00:12:15,050
But now you've opened up to him!

149
00:12:15,050 --> 00:12:18,010
Though it might have raised
a few more questions...

150
00:12:18,010 --> 00:12:21,280
I didn't want to raise more questions.

151
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:26,250
Now to figure out how to reignite his drive.

152
00:12:26,250 --> 00:12:29,390
You make it sound so simple.

153
00:12:29,390 --> 00:12:31,530
It's a high hurdle to overcome.

154
00:12:31,530 --> 00:12:35,930
Walls in front of you may look tall.

155
00:12:35,930 --> 00:12:39,570
But at least there's a wall you can see!

156
00:12:39,570 --> 00:12:40,900
Such positivity.

157
00:12:40,900 --> 00:12:43,430
You'll just have to overcome it.

158
00:13:09,550 --> 00:13:14,780
- A tall wall...
- <i>You'll just have to overcome it.</i>

159
00:13:18,930 --> 00:13:21,030
Haru?

160
00:13:21,030 --> 00:13:22,910
I...

161
00:13:22,910 --> 00:13:26,260
I have a sex drive.

162
00:13:26,260 --> 00:13:28,840
- Huh?
- Don't "huh?" me!

163
00:13:29,940 --> 00:13:33,550
We're married. I love you.

164
00:13:33,550 --> 00:13:35,740
Take me!

165
00:13:35,740 --> 00:13:38,210
I want to have sex with you!

166
00:13:52,620 --> 00:13:55,000
Will putting it in satisfy you?

167
00:14:34,270 --> 00:14:37,280
<i>That felt too real.</i>

168
00:14:37,280 --> 00:14:40,940
<i>More pressingly, I can't believe I...</i>

169
00:14:53,860 --> 00:14:55,400
My bad.

170
00:14:59,640 --> 00:15:03,810
<i>Ouji, in a suit? What a feast for the eyes!</i>

171
00:15:03,810 --> 00:15:06,700
<i>Wait, I'm not wearing anything underneath.</i>

172
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:15,080
Lock the door, would you?

173
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:18,110
Only old dramas do the whole,
"bathroom surprise" plot.

174
00:15:18,110 --> 00:15:19,940
Sorry.

175
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:24,020
The suit looks nice on you.

176
00:15:24,020 --> 00:15:28,310
Thanks. I'm seeing some higher-ups
at that idol's recording session.

177
00:15:28,310 --> 00:15:30,370
I'll probably be home late tonight.

178
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:46,880
<i>Yes, I totally understand.</i>

179
00:15:46,880 --> 00:15:51,100
<i>If you're comfortable enough
to laugh off the awkwardness,</i>

180
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:54,980
<i>finding happiness without sex
is entirely possible, isn't it?</i>

181
00:15:54,980 --> 00:15:56,760
Is it?

182
00:15:56,760 --> 00:16:00,080
<i>What are your honest feelings, Haru?</i>

183
00:16:00,080 --> 00:16:02,850
<i>I...</i>

184
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:07,450
I want to do it.

185
00:16:07,450 --> 00:16:09,260
Do what?

186
00:16:11,700 --> 00:16:15,220
Nothing, pay me no mind.

187
00:16:17,300 --> 00:16:19,080
If you insist.

188
00:16:20,880 --> 00:16:25,630
<i>They cannot ever have sex again,
unless they divorce their husbands.</i>

189
00:16:25,630 --> 00:16:30,050
<i>Isn't that incredibly terrifying for a woman?</i>

190
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:43,200
Welcome.

191
00:16:43,850 --> 00:16:45,680
Haru?

192
00:16:45,680 --> 00:16:46,960
Akina?

193
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:49,370
You're drinking alone? That's unusual.

194
00:16:49,370 --> 00:16:52,680
I needed the alcohol.

195
00:16:54,510 --> 00:16:59,870
What? You haven't had sex with Ouji?

196
00:16:59,870 --> 00:17:02,350
I know you think it's ridiculous,
given we're newlyweds.

197
00:17:02,350 --> 00:17:04,370
I haven't said anything yet.

198
00:17:04,370 --> 00:17:07,840
I know, but what can I do?

199
00:17:07,840 --> 00:17:09,940
He's saying he has no sex drive.

200
00:17:09,940 --> 00:17:13,910
It's probably just withered dry.

201
00:17:13,910 --> 00:17:17,630
- What?
- Water it, and he'll perk right back up.

202
00:17:17,630 --> 00:17:20,780
You're giving high level advice, too?

203
00:17:20,780 --> 00:17:23,270
Is it really high level though?

204
00:17:23,270 --> 00:17:27,920
Unlike romance, sex is simple.

205
00:17:27,920 --> 00:17:32,500
He lusts, you're lusted after,
and you both satiate those desires.

206
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:33,990
That's why I love it.

207
00:17:33,990 --> 00:17:37,770
It's the "lusted after" part I struggle with.

208
00:17:38,460 --> 00:17:41,870
He didn't even react
when I wore nothing but a sweater.

209
00:17:41,870 --> 00:17:46,120
Then I guess you'll just have to try harder.

210
00:17:46,120 --> 00:17:48,380
I can't.

211
00:17:48,380 --> 00:17:56,080
To have lust, and to be lusted for.
They're supposed to be equal, right?

212
00:17:56,080 --> 00:17:57,880
That, they are.

213
00:18:00,140 --> 00:18:05,110
But we've never been equal.

214
00:18:08,220 --> 00:18:11,140
<i>Ouji was always at the center of everything.</i>

215
00:18:12,460 --> 00:18:15,430
<i>I could only ever watch from the sidelines.</i>

216
00:18:19,490 --> 00:18:23,060
<i>Sometimes, I wasn't even permitted a glance.</i>

217
00:18:23,060 --> 00:18:24,590
Ouji...

218
00:18:26,900 --> 00:18:29,350
You're a bit too persistent.

219
00:18:31,410 --> 00:18:33,550
<i>Ouji was the main character.</i>

220
00:18:33,550 --> 00:18:37,000
<i>And I was the background extra.</i>

221
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:42,200
Ouji controls the flow of the story.

222
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:45,860
You don't give yourself any credit.

223
00:18:45,860 --> 00:18:49,290
Haru, do you want to have sex?

224
00:18:49,290 --> 00:18:53,840
Or do you want to be loved by your husband?

225
00:18:55,130 --> 00:18:58,810
If it's the latter,
then I can't say I really get it.

226
00:18:59,450 --> 00:19:03,380
Unlike sex, romance is never simple,

227
00:19:03,380 --> 00:19:07,250
even if you are a married couple.

228
00:19:07,250 --> 00:19:09,240
Personally, I hate conflating

229
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:11,810
my bodily desires with that of the heart.

230
00:19:11,810 --> 00:19:13,840
I'm surprised you can keep them apart.

231
00:19:13,840 --> 00:19:19,280
Sure, you may want to have sex,

232
00:19:19,280 --> 00:19:20,910
but only with your husband, right?

233
00:19:20,910 --> 00:19:23,080
Of course. I never considered another option.

234
00:19:23,080 --> 00:19:28,450
And you also want to share
a mutual love with him, right?

235
00:19:31,990 --> 00:19:34,260
Right.

236
00:19:34,260 --> 00:19:37,940
Then you're not helping your case,
calling yourself a background extra.

237
00:19:37,940 --> 00:19:40,630
Why'd you even marry him in the first place?

238
00:19:40,630 --> 00:19:46,160
I married Ouji because he proposed to me.

239
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:48,880
Sounds like he loves you plenty.

240
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:51,150
That's not the issue here.

241
00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:57,500
<i>Not for these last few years, no.</i>

242
00:19:57,500 --> 00:20:00,390
- <i>What?</i>
- <i>Well, that's not the only reason.</i>

243
00:20:01,920 --> 00:20:05,360
<i>It's just easy being with you, Haru.</i>

244
00:20:06,330 --> 00:20:09,000
He says being with me, is "easy".

245
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:11,860
Easy.

246
00:20:13,900 --> 00:20:18,080
Maybe he's tired
dealing with aggressive women?

247
00:20:18,080 --> 00:20:20,450
You are the more demure type.

248
00:20:20,450 --> 00:20:23,820
Akina. You can learn to be less blunt.

249
00:20:23,820 --> 00:20:26,200
Sorry.

250
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:33,740
Maybe he never saw me
with that intent at all.

251
00:20:38,580 --> 00:20:40,460
Say something.

252
00:20:40,460 --> 00:20:42,850
You told me to be less blunt.

253
00:20:42,850 --> 00:20:44,740
That never stopped you before.

254
00:20:44,740 --> 00:20:50,180
Still, this is only your current predicament.

255
00:20:50,180 --> 00:20:52,010
You never know what the future holds.

256
00:20:52,010 --> 00:20:54,230
It's been five years since I met him.

257
00:20:54,230 --> 00:20:56,900
Will he change? We haven't even held hands.

258
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:59,130
The furthest he gets is a head pat.

259
00:20:59,130 --> 00:21:00,530
- I gotta go.
- That's it?

260
00:21:00,530 --> 00:21:02,360
Good luck. I'm rooting for you.

261
00:21:02,360 --> 00:21:05,020
- Are you, really?
- Toodles!

262
00:21:18,790 --> 00:21:22,110
<i>This is only your current predicament.</i>

263
00:21:22,110 --> 00:21:24,720
<i>You never know what the future holds.</i>

264
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:27,220
But after five years of nothing?

265
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:04,000
Good evening. The name's Naoki,
from Ebisu Boys Club.

266
00:22:12,900 --> 00:22:15,940
Welcome home, Haruchan!

267
00:22:15,940 --> 00:22:19,550
<i>"Haruchan"? Why the nickname?</i>

268
00:22:19,550 --> 00:22:22,180
I thought you said you'd be late.

269
00:22:23,150 --> 00:22:25,270
I got worn out.

270
00:22:25,270 --> 00:22:28,260
Home is where I can relax.

271
00:22:28,260 --> 00:22:30,680
I see.

272
00:22:30,680 --> 00:22:34,160
Join me for a drink, Haruchan.

273
00:22:35,450 --> 00:22:39,510
Ouji, did you make a blunder?

274
00:22:40,270 --> 00:22:41,280
Huh?

275
00:22:41,280 --> 00:22:46,550
You only use "chan"
when things have gone wrong.

276
00:22:46,550 --> 00:22:48,200
Seriously?

277
00:22:48,970 --> 00:22:50,880
Well...

278
00:22:50,880 --> 00:22:55,610
Recently, a capable girl in her twenties
joined our agency.

279
00:22:55,610 --> 00:23:02,080
And today, she got mad at me
for always addressing her as "you".

280
00:23:02,080 --> 00:23:06,280
Just made me realize
how I sometimes do that to you, too.

281
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:09,070
You're having this realization, now?

282
00:23:14,730 --> 00:23:16,730
She's entirely right, you know.

283
00:23:16,730 --> 00:23:19,730
Our generation has to adapt to new standards.

284
00:23:19,730 --> 00:23:22,630
I know that now, but still...

285
00:23:33,690 --> 00:23:35,950
You're seriously a calming presence.

286
00:23:35,950 --> 00:23:38,980
And you're doing it again!

287
00:24:38,970 --> 00:24:59,100
[Preview]
